<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Mirror probe configuration
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
Mirror probe configuration registers per probe index.

In addition to the mirror probe configuration parameters provided in this register group, it is also possible to trigger frame mirroring using 
VCAP_S2 -> MIRROR_PROBE action
ANA_L3:VLAN:VLAN_CFG.VLAN_MIRROR_ENA

The mirror port, to which mirrored frames are copied, is configured using these parameters:
QFWD:SYSTEM:FRAME_COPY_CFG
ANA_AC:PS_COMMON:VSTAX_GMIRROR_CFG (when using VStaX)

Encapsulation mirrored frames can be configured using these parameters:
REW:COMMON:MIRROR_PROBE_CFG
REW:COMMON:MIRROR_TAG_A_CFG
REW:COMMON:MIRROR_TAG_B_CFG
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
Mirror probe configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Mirror traffic received from CPU by this mirror probe.

PROBE_RX_CPU_AND_VD works as an extension of the PROBE_PORT_MASK to cover CPU ports and VD0/VD1.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
"00000": No RX mirror
"xxxx1": Rx from CPU port 53 is mirrored
"xxx1x": Rx from CPU port 54 is mirrored
"xx1xx": Rx from VD0 is mirrored
"x1xxx": Rx from VD1 is mirrored
"1xxxx": Rx from VD2 is mirrored
Only works with RX mirror enabled. See ANA_AC:MIRROR_PROBE:PROBE_CFG.PROBE_DIRECTION.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
The set of CPU extraction ports from where traffic is Tx mirrored by this mirror probe.

Only works when Tx mirroring is  enabled. 

Related parameters:
ANA_AC:MIRROR_PROBE:PROBE_CFG.PROBE_DIRECTION
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: CPU extraction port is not Tx mirrored
1: CPU extraction port is Tx mirrored
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
The mirror probe's VLAN ID when PROBE_VLAN_MODE is 10 or 11.

Probing per VLAN can also be enabled in ANA_L3:VLAN, but such configuration will affect all mirror probes.

Related parameters:
ANA_AC:MIRROR_PROBE:PROBE_CFG.PROBE_VLAN_MODE
ANA_L3:VLAN:VLAN_CFG.VLAN_MIRROR_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Mirror probe's VLAN filtering mode.

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:VLAN:VLAN_CFG.VLAN_MIRROR_ENA
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
00 : No VLAN filtering
01 : Mirror only traffic in VLANs with ANA_L3:VLAN:VLAN_CFG.VLAN_MIRROR_ENA set
10 : Mirror only traffic with CL-IVID = PROBE_VID.
11 : Reserved.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Mirror probe's MAC address filtering mode, based on the mirror bit in the MAC table.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
"00" : No MAC filtering
"01" : Mirror only traffic with mirror bit set for known DMAC
"10" : Mirror only traffic with mirror bit set for known SMAC
"11" : Mirror only traffic with mirror bit set for known DMAC and/or known SMAC
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Direction of traffic that is mirrored.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
"00" : Mirroring is disabled.
"01" : TX - Only traffic to destination ports in the probe port set
"10" : RX - Only traffic from source ports in the probe port set
"11" : RX+TX - Traffic to and from ports in the probe port set (always mirrored as RX)
