<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Aggregation port masks
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
The aggregation port masks are applied to the destination port mask to ensure that frames only get forwarded to _one_ port within the LLAG (Local Link Aggregation Group). 
I.e. these masks must have only 1 bit set for each logical port.

The frame's AC is used to select which aggregation port mask to apply.

In stacking configurations, the bits for the stack links must always be set. 
The only exception to this is when a LLAG stack link is used for interconnecting stack units. In this case each mask must only have one of the physical stack ports enabled.
