Configuration for Global Link Aggregation Groups
------------------------------
<reg_short_dscr>:
GLAG member count configuration
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
GLAG member count.

This is used to select the GLAG port mask within the GLAG part of ANA_AC:PGID.

Using GLAG_MBR_CNT a GLAG_MBR_IDX is calculated as follows:
GLAG_MBR_IDX = frame.ac % GLAG_MBR_CNT

The frame's GLAGID and GLAG_MBR_IDX are then used for lookup in ANA_AC:PGID.
------------------------------
<field_enc>:
0: One member
1: Two members
...
7: Eight members
------------------------------
<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Port group ID table configurations
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
Port Group ID table registers

Unicast:
Entry 0 contains port 0 destination mask
Entry 1 contains port 1 destination mask
...
Entry 65-1 contains port 65-1 destination mask

Flood and general purpose (multicast):
Entry 65 contains UC_FLOOD_MASK
Entry 65+1 contains L2_MC_FLOOD_MASK
Entry 65+2 contains IP4_MC_DATA_FLOOD_MASK
Entry 65+3 contains IP4_MC_CTRL_FLOOD_MASK
Entry 65+4 contains IP6_MC_DATA_FLOOD_MASK
Entry 65+5 contains IP6_MC_CTRL_FLOOD_MASK
Entry 65+6 contains general purpose PGID mask 6
Entry 65+7 contains general purpose PGID mask 7
...
Entry 65+2048-1 contains general purpose PGID mask 2048-1

Forwarder virtual LAG profiles (FV_LAG):
Note: Overloads part of the general purpose area.

Each FV_LAG profile contains 65+6 entries for unicast and flood. The FV_LAG profile index comes from ANA_L3:VLAN:MISC.FV_LAG_IDX and is applied when FV_LAG_IDX > 0. 
Given the FV_LAG_IDX, an offset into the PGID table is calculated:
  FV_LAG_OFFSET = 65+1024+(FV_LAG_IDX-1)*(65+6).

Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET contains port 0 destination mask for FV_LAG profile
...
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65-1 contains port 65-1 destination mask for FV_LAG profile
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65 contains UC_FLOOD_MASK for FV_LAG profile
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65+1 contains L2_MC_FLOOD_MASK for FV_LAG profile
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65+2 contains IP4_MC_DATA_FLOOD_MASK for FV_LAG profile
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65+3 contains IP4_MC_CTRL_FLOOD_MASK for FV_LAG profile
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65+4 contains IP6_MC_DATA_FLOOD_MASK for FV_LAG profile
Entry FV_LAG_OFFSET+65+5 contains IP6_MC_CTRL_FLOOD_MASK for FV_LAG profile

GLAG:
Note: Overloads part of the general purpose area.

Entry 65+1024-8*32 contains GLAG 0 member 0
Entry 65+1024-8*32+1 contains GLAG 0 member 1
...
Entry 65+1024-1 contains GLAG 32-1 member 7

The port masks 0 to  65-1 are initialized to a walking one.
