<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Conversation-sensitive distribution table
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
The CSD port masks are applied to the destination port mask as part of conversation-sensitive distribution for link aggregation. These masks should only have 1 bit set for each logical port.

The frame's conversation ID is used as index into the table. The conversation ID is the VID from the resulting outer VLAN tag after applying any VLAN pop counts. If frame becomes untagged, conversation ID = 0 is used.
