<reggrp_short_dscr>:
LAG reset port masks
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
The LAG reset port mask is OR'ed with the aggregation (ANA_AC:AGGR) and CSD masks (ANA_AC:CSD) before applying the result to the final destination port mask. The purpose of the LAG reset port mask is to allow a VLAN to remove specific LAGs from its forwarding domain. In addition to setting the LAG reset port mask, a forwarder virtual LAG must also configure unicast port masks and flood masks in the associated PGID space in ANA_AC:PGID.

The LAG reset table is looked up with the forwarder virtual LAG index provided by ANA_L3:VLAN:MISC.FV_LAG_IDX.
